54 inline void setToHome(moveit::core::RobotState& panda_state)
55 {
56  panda_state.setToDefaultValues();
57  double joint2 = -0.785;
58  double joint4 = -2.356;
59  double joint6 = 1.571;
60  double joint7 = 0.785;
61  panda_state.setJointPositions("panda_joint2", &joint2);
62  panda_state.setJointPositions("panda_joint4", &joint4);
63  panda_state.setJointPositions("panda_joint6", &joint6);
64  panda_state.setJointPositions("panda_joint7", &joint7);
65  panda_state.update();
66 }

68 template <class CollisionAllocatorType>
69 class CollisionDetectorPandaTest : public testing::Test
70 {
71 public:
72  std::shared_ptr<CollisionAllocatorType> value_;
73 
74 protected:
75  void SetUp() override
76  {
77  value_ = std::make_shared<CollisionAllocatorType>();
78  robot_model_ = moveit::core::loadTestingRobotModel("panda");
79  robot_model_ok_ = static_cast<bool>(robot_model_);
80 
81  acm_ = std::make_shared<collision_detection::AllowedCollisionMatrix>();
82  // Use default collision operations in the SRDF to setup the acm
83  const std::vector<std::string>& collision_links = robot_model_->getLinkModelNamesWithCollisionGeometry();
84  acm_->setEntry(collision_links, collision_links, false);
85 
86  // allow collisions for pairs that have been disabled
87  const std::vector<srdf::Model::DisabledCollision>& dc = robot_model_->getSRDF()->getDisabledCollisionPairs();
88  for (const srdf::Model::DisabledCollision& it : dc)
89  acm_->setEntry(it.link1_, it.link2_, true);
90 
91  cenv_ = value_->allocateEnv(robot_model_);
92 
93  robot_state_ = std::make_shared<moveit::core::RobotState>(robot_model_);
94  setToHome(*robot_state_);
95  }
96 
97  void TearDown() override
98  {
99  }

104

151  shapes::Shape* shape = new shapes::Box(.1, .1, .1);
152  shapes::ShapeConstPtr shape_ptr(shape);
153 
154  Eigen::Isometry3d pos1 = Eigen::Isometry3d::Identity();
155  pos1.translation().z() = 0.3;
156  this->cenv_->getWorld()->addToObject("box", pos1, shape_ptr, Eigen::Isometry3d::Identity());
157 
158  this->cenv_->checkSelfCollision(req, res, *this->robot_state_, *this->acm_);
159  ASSERT_FALSE(res.collision);
160  res.clear();
161 
162  this->cenv_->checkRobotCollision(req, res, *this->robot_state_, *this->acm_);
163  ASSERT_TRUE(res.collision);
164  res.clear();
165 
166  this->cenv_->getWorld()->moveObject("box", pos1);
167  this->cenv_->checkRobotCollision(req, res, *this->robot_state_, *this->acm_);
168  ASSERT_TRUE(res.collision);
169  res.clear();
170 
171  this->cenv_->getWorld()->moveObject("box", pos1);
172  ASSERT_FALSE(res.collision);
173 }

269 TYPED_TEST_P(DistanceCheckPandaTest, DistanceSingle)
270 {
271  std::set<const moveit::core::LinkModel*> active_components{ this->robot_model_->getLinkModel("panda_hand") };
272  collision_detection::DistanceRequest req;
273  req.type = collision_detection::DistanceRequestTypes::SINGLE;
274  req.active_components_only = &active_components;
275  req.enable_signed_distance = true;
276 
277  random_numbers::RandomNumberGenerator rng(0x47110815);
278  double min_distance = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
279  for (int i = 0; i < 10; ++i)
280  {
281  collision_detection::DistanceResult res;
282 
283  shapes::ShapeConstPtr shape(new shapes::Cylinder(rng.uniform01(), rng.uniform01()));
284  Eigen::Isometry3d pose{ Eigen::Isometry3d::Identity() };
285  pose.translation() =
286  Eigen::Vector3d(rng.uniformReal(0.1, 2.0), rng.uniformReal(0.1, 2.0), rng.uniformReal(1.2, 1.7));
287  double quat[4];
288  rng.quaternion(quat);
289  pose.linear() = Eigen::Quaterniond(quat[0], quat[1], quat[2], quat[3]).toRotationMatrix();
290 
291  this->cenv_->getWorld()->addToObject("collection", Eigen::Isometry3d::Identity(), shape, pose);
292  this->cenv_->getWorld()->removeObject("object");
293  this->cenv_->getWorld()->addToObject("object", pose, shape, Eigen::Isometry3d::Identity());
294 
295  this->cenv_->distanceRobot(req, res, *this->robot_state_);
296  auto& distances1 = res.distances[std::pair<std::string, std::string>("collection", "panda_hand")];
297  auto& distances2 = res.distances[std::pair<std::string, std::string>("object", "panda_hand")];
298  ASSERT_EQ(distances1.size(), 1u) << "no distance reported for collection/panda_hand";
299  ASSERT_EQ(distances2.size(), 1u) << "no distance reported for object/panda_hand";
300 
301  double collection_distance = distances1[0].distance;
302  min_distance = std::min(min_distance, distances2[0].distance);
303  ASSERT_NEAR(collection_distance, min_distance, 1e-5)
304  << "distance to collection is greater than distance to minimum of individual objects after " << i << " rounds";
305  }
306 }

308 // FCL < 0.6 completely fails the DistancePoints test, so we have two test
309 // suites, one with and one without the test.
310 template <class CollisionAllocatorType>
311 class DistanceFullPandaTest : public DistanceCheckPandaTest<CollisionAllocatorType>
312 {
313 };
314 
315 TYPED_TEST_CASE_P(DistanceFullPandaTest);
316 
318 TYPED_TEST_P(DistanceFullPandaTest, DistancePoints)
319 {
320  // Adding the box right in front of the robot hand
321  shapes::Box* shape = new shapes::Box(0.1, 0.1, 0.1);
322  shapes::ShapeConstPtr shape_ptr(shape);
323 
324  Eigen::Isometry3d pos{ Eigen::Isometry3d::Identity() };
325  pos.translation().x() = 0.43;
326  pos.translation().y() = 0;
327  pos.translation().z() = 0.55;
328  this->cenv_->getWorld()->addToObject("box", shape_ptr, pos);
329 
330  collision_detection::DistanceRequest req;
331  req.acm = &*this->acm_;
332  req.type = collision_detection::DistanceRequestTypes::SINGLE;
333  req.enable_nearest_points = true;
334  req.max_contacts_per_body = 1;
335 
336  collision_detection::DistanceResult res;
337  this->cenv_->distanceRobot(req, res, *this->robot_state_);
338 
339  // Checks a particular point is inside the box
340  auto check_in_box = [&](const Eigen::Vector3d& p) {
341  Eigen::Vector3d in_box = pos.inverse() * p;
342 
343  constexpr double eps = 1e-5;
344  EXPECT_LE(std::abs(in_box.x()), shape->size[0] + eps);
345  EXPECT_LE(std::abs(in_box.y()), shape->size[1] + eps);
346  EXPECT_LE(std::abs(in_box.z()), shape->size[2] + eps);
347  };
348 
349  // Check that all points reported on "box" are actually on the box and not
350  // on the robot
351  for (auto& distance : res.distances)
352  {
353  for (auto& pair : distance.second)
354  {
355  if (pair.link_names[0] == "box")
356  check_in_box(pair.nearest_points[0]);
357  else if (pair.link_names[1] == "box")
358  check_in_box(pair.nearest_points[1]);
359  else
360  ADD_FAILURE() << "Unrecognized link names";
361  }
362  }
363 }
